courseSummaryDetails.courseDescription: Computer programming for students with some previous programming experience. Emphasizes program design, style, and decomposition. Uses data structures (e.g., lists, dictionaries, sets) to solve computational problems motivated by modern societal and scientific needs. Introduces data abstraction and interface versus implementation. Cannot be taken for credit if credit received for <span class="linkified" data-id="29c0b2f0-7cad-4784-af82-146fbd550b7e" data-subject="CSE" data-number="143"  data-title="Computer Programming II" data-text="CSE 143" />.
courseSummaryDetails.recommendedPrep: <span class="linkified" data-id="2a94a8e8-66d8-4c03-9da1-ac1e32e5e171" data-subject="CSE" data-number="121"  data-title="Introduction to Computer Programming I" data-text="CSE 121" /> or completion of Paul G. Allen School's Guided Self-Placement.
